<headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 31 at 5:54PM EDT  by NWS Greenville-Spartanburg</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of northwestern
Cabarrus, southeastern Catawba, southeastern Iredell, north central
Mecklenburg and southwestern Rowan Counties through 645 PM EDT...
At 554 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 11
miles north of Huntersville, or near Lake Norman, moving east at 30
mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.
Locations impacted include...
Kannapolis, Downtown Concord, Salisbury, Mooresville, Davidson, China
Grove, Landis, Enochville, Lake Norman and Coddle Creek Reservoir.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.00 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
